444,IssueCommentEvent,2016-12-27 02:16:36+00:00,44054354,dabeaz/curio,350836,dabeaz,,,192122539,269258756,"But there is a stream abstraction.  You can call `sock.as_stream()` to create a stream from a socket.   The resulting object (`SocketStream`) uses the same API as the ""file"" objects used for pipes.   There is also the asynchronous ""file"" object in the `curio.file` which has a similar API.   In theory, it should be possible to interchange and/or connect any combination of these things.  ",{},,User,False
