956,IssueCommentEvent,2016-11-23 03:26:16+00:00,19384977,peplin/pygatt,184212,peplin,,,190963905,262427519,"Thanks for the PR!

Could you show me an example of what you are trying to do? It looks like the args are going to be static (since you are setting them at subscribe time) and they don't depend on anything in the BLE stack, so I'll bet you can create a partial function to accomplish this. It seems a little odd, at a glance, to stash static arguments inside pygatt.

Would something like this work for you?

```
def callback(message, food_type):
    pass

pizza_callback = functools.partial(callback, food_type=""pizza"")

backend.subscribe(..., callback=pizza_callback)
```",{},,User,False
