974,IssueCommentEvent,2016-09-20 15:13:51+00:00,22937749,rasbt/mlxtend,5618407,rasbt,,,177904071,248332357,"> I have a question though. I'm new to this so I'm not sure but what exactly are the Appveyor and TravisCI tests for and how do I make sure I don't break them?

No worries, these are just automated test and you can think of them as running `nosetests` locally. It's a check for me that everything runs correctly, but it also runs the unittests on different systems (e.g., AppVeyor runs on Windows and Travis CI runs on Linux). Also, the Travis checks make sure that the code works for both Python 2.7 and 3.5. If you are interested, the configuration file is here: https://github.com/rasbt/mlxtend/blob/master/.travis.yml

I just merged the pull request that moved plotting functions to `mlxtend.plotting`. I guess you need to do a rebase now, which basically means that you apply the changes from the master branch to your branch, and put your changes on top of it. 

- I.e., you would have to sync your repo with the upstream master branch first: see info for syncing here: https://rasbt.github.io/mlxtend/contributing/#syncing-an-existing-fork
- then `git checkout <your branch>`
- then  `git rebase upstream/master`

Thanks again for your contribution, I will take a look at the actual code soon!",{},,User,False
