1937,IssueCommentEvent,2015-01-07 00:25:24+00:00,22447892,adamhajari/spyre,1072820,adamhajari,,,52703161,68959689,"@huntcsg I think there's an even cleaner way to do this.

If we make this the default getPlot method

````
def getPlot(self, params):
	return eval(""self.""+str(params['output_id'])+""()"")
````

Then you can either override getPlot (the normal way), or if you want multiple plots, leave getPlot as is and create a new function for each plot output element:

````
def output_1(self, params):
    #code to generate a plot
    return figure

def output_2(self, params):
    #code to generate a different plot
    return figure
````

We can do the same thing with getHTML, getData, etc...

Should be straight forward to implement. I'll work on it this week.",{},,User,False
