1953,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-27 18:01:57+00:00,9923468,boppreh/keyboard,7684744,glitchassassin,,,268894417,354151730,"Why not just make the canonical names different for each platform, but reversible?

For example, the canonical name on Mac for ""command"", ""windows"", ""cmd"", or ""win"" would be ""command"". On Windows, the canonical name for all of the above would be ""windows"".

This would correctly report a ""windows"" key press on Windows, and a ""command"" key press on Mac, but cross-platform code would work fine: whether you specified a hotkey with ""cmd"" or ""win"" it would trigger appropriately on either platform.

I've updated my pull request with an example of what I'm talking about.",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
