2445,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-28 17:06:53+00:00,84231584,deadc0de6/dotdrop,8973919,deadc0de6,,,284758717,354321355,"I added an option to dotdrop to pass arguments to `diff` in the branch [diffopts](https://github.com/deadc0de6/dotdrop/tree/diffopts). This should allow to pass any arguments to `diff` through the switch `-o`. Note that the option `-r, --recursive` is always activated when comparing.

for example:
```
dotdrop compare -o ""-c5 -a""
```

will execute `diff -r -c5 -a` on the dotfiles to compare.

Can you test it out and let me know if that matches what you needed ?",{},OWNER,User,False
