2913,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-10 17:22:15+00:00,1938370,Mottie/tablesorter,136959,Mottie,,,105851467,139316697,"When setting `class=""sorter-false""`, it is actually the lowest priority setting - check out [this demo](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-options-headers.html). So what that means is if you have a `headers` setting that sets a parser for that column, it will override that class.

If you shared the HTML of the `thead` and the initialization code, I might be able to help find the problem.

Also, don't forget you can always use the [`debug` option](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/index.html#debug) to see what is happening when tablesorter initializes.

```js
$('table').tablesorter({
  // other options...
  debug: true
});",{},,User,False
