2994,IssueCommentEvent,2016-12-12 16:54:31+00:00,12366195,danielfrg/word2vec,1277725,mrmattwright,,,191865111,266484842,"Ok this is to do with encoding....unfortunately the default training encodes binary files as 'ISO-8859-1' vs UTF-8. 

This is a bit annoying because if you use code like this and train your own model: 

```
 word2vec.word2vec('normalised_phrases2.txt',
                      temp_vec,
                      size=500)
```

then try and load it like this

```
model = word2vec.load(vector_file)
```

You'll get the error above. There is an answer though...which is to change the way you load a model to this: 

```
model = word2vec.WordVectors.from_binary(vector_file,encoding=""ISO-8859-1"")
```

The default for when you do `word2vec.load` and kind=""bin"" should probably be changed so this is the default behaviour. ",{},,User,False
