3203,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-12 20:05:24+00:00,6794278,scanny/python-pptx,2062718,scanny,,,207041240,279244302,"@gsd4me When I said as simple as possible, I was thinking something more like this:

```python
from pptx import Presentation
from pptx.enum.shapes import MSO_SHAPE
from pptx.util import Inches


prs = Presentation()
slide = prs.slides.add_slide(prs.slide_layouts[5])
shape = slide.add_shape(
    MSO_SHAPE.ROUNDED_RECTANGLE, Inches(1), Inches(1), Inches(1), Inches(1)
)
paragraph = shape.text_frame.paragraphs[0]
run = paragraph.add_run()
run.text = 'foobar'
prs.save('adb.pptx')
```

You need to do more work on your side to narrow down where the problem is. Get rid of all the loops and conditionals for a start. As near as I can tell, your code is exiting before it ever calls the statements you say aren't working.

You might add some print statements on your side just to make sure you're actually getting to the code you expect you are.",{},,User,False
