3551,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-14 15:55:49+00:00,21058725,hustlzp/Flask-Boost,1180240,hustlzp,,,140555460,196381684,"You can use sqlacodegen to generate model codes to a single python file:

```sh
sqlacodegen mysql://root:@localhost/database --outfile ./application/models/models.py
```

[application/models/_base.py](https://github.com/hustlzp/Flask-Boost/blob/master/flask_boost/project/application/models/_base.py) remains the same, and [application/models/\_\_init\_\_.py](https://github.com/hustlzp/Flask-Boost/blob/master/flask_boost/project/application/models/__init__.py) can be:

```py
from ._base import db
from .models import *
```

If so, there is no need to use `boost new model accounts` command.

Then you can make a query in controller (such as [application/controllers/account.py](https://github.com/hustlzp/Flask-Boost/blob/master/flask_boost/project/application/controllers/account.py)) as follows:

```py
from ..models import db, User

db.session.query(User).filter(User.id == 1)
```

Hope that'll be helpful to you.",{},,User,False
