5400,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-26 21:28:49+00:00,37035856,gkovacs/lz-string-python,23198259,HiroKajino,,,224286712,297546574,"That was a mistake, I'm sorry about that. I meant to push it to our
project's fork. Thank you for checking in, anyways.

Maybe I should share the reason why I was making an edit, though. Our team
was having an issue with LZString.decopressFromBase64 method, that when a
very large data is passed in, the processing speed declined enough that our
server was timing out. Then my colleague had an idea that the performance
decline might be due to excess string concatenation. We changed the
variables that gather the result ('result' in decompress() and 'output' in
decompressFromBase64()) from string to list, and instead of concatenating
string, list is appended with a new character. (
https://github.com/pacerrabbit/lz-string-python/blob/lzstring-nextlesson/lzstring/__init__.py#L546)
With this, the performance increased significantly, and we started using
the edited version on our project.

- Hiro

