6045,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-19 21:41:47+00:00,22954701,noirbizarre/flask-restplus,22421878,zack3241,,,262797522,338046233,"For anyone cares what specifically the bug he's referring to in v0.10.1, it's caused by the flask_restplus.reqparse.Argument.handle_validation_error method returning back error as a `str` instead of a `ValueError` when you set `bundle_errors=True`. A work around is to use `bundle_errors=False` until the changes have been pushed to pypi. It won't return all the errors but it will at least return back a 400 response code.",{},NONE,User,False
