6052,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-14 19:18:05+00:00,7744414,peterbe/django-fancy-cache,26739,peterbe,,,148019684,210107556,"I don't think it's worthwhile to build something specifically for the Admin. Not many people use it. 

What I do in my own use of django-fancy-cache is that I know a certain key to use in my prefix.

E.g.
```python
@receiver(post_save, sender=LogEntry, dispatch_uid=""clear_fancy_cache"")
def clear_fancy_cache(sender, instance, **kwargs):
    cache_key = 'mykey-%s' % instance.id
    cache.delete(cache_key)
```
and in my key_prefixer, I have something like this:
def key_prefixer(request):
    model = MyModel.objects.get(slug=request.path)
    return 'mykey-%s' % model.id
```

You can see more in [code for my blog](https://github.com/peterbe/django-peterbecom/blob/6709a7064510ec15b411d20b96fd4bb05c14d2b6/peterbecom/apps/plog/views.py#L46).",{},,User,False
