6537,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-17 13:51:52+00:00,8177778,koalalorenzo/python-digitalocean,33528,koalalorenzo,,,148711112,211022422,"> It would be in user's best interest to have the flexibility to temporarily exercise unexposed parts of our REST api when a product is released without having to completely and unnecessarily re-run $pip install or $ apt-get install until the new version of the bindings is released.

I highly disagree, this would lead the project to bigger problems since developers should use specific versions to implement specific rules and method based on their needs. For example, If this changes is applied, then they will not update when the third version will be released and the old API deprecated, and nobody will contribute... since ""one line of code can change it"".

If a deeper implementation is missing, like #132 for example, people edit the open source code and a new minor version for everybody needs is released! That is the spirit.

Allowing users to use custom options out of the blue is just a bad idea, for the library (to allow users to use the version they want, and keep the module updated) and to avoid security problems. At the moment, I am not going to merge this since I think ""Your Company"" (I still don't know who you are, since your profiles are empty, _are you working at DO?_ ) would be the only one using this... and if developers can ""just modify the behavior"" without updating and contribute with the others, it's just a big loss for the development process of this module. :cry: ",{},,User,False
