6761,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-10 15:08:15+00:00,18853469,umutbozkurt/django-rest-framework-mongoengine,7602655,BurkovBA,,,219225428,292978761,"@MohamedShawky 

Hi, Mohamed. I'm working on this in [django-rest-framework-mongoengine-example](https://github.com/BurkovBA/django-rest-framework-mongoengine-examplel) project.

I've just started, but you can already take a look into [users app](https://github.com/BurkovBA/django-rest-framework-mongoengine-example/tree/master/project/users) there. Already, you can understand some things about how to integrate Mongoengine authentication system with django from that example.

That example replicates DRF's [authtoken](https://github.com/encode/django-rest-framework/tree/master/rest_framework/authtoken) app, which implements JSON [TokenAuthentication](https://github.com/encode/django-rest-framework/blob/master/rest_framework/authentication.py#L143) scheme - when your client identifies user by a token, typically stored in your JS app or in LocalStorage/SessionStorage and sends it to server in `Authentication` header upon each request to itself. This Token is generated by server side of your application and returned to the client in exchange for a correct username/password combination by ObtainAuthToken view.",{},,User,False
