6867,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-12 18:41:14+00:00,27609645,web2py/pydal,10407290,stephenrauch,33118,web2py,105573628,139808995,"@franciscocosta 

I am still unable to duplicate this. It would be helpful to see the table definition for the table failing in the update.  Also, can you reproduce the error after changing in `object_id()`:

```python                      
                      
if not isinstance(arg, (int, long)):
    try:
        if isinstance(arg, Row):
            return self.object_id(long(arg))
    except:
        pass
    raise TypeError(""object_id argument must be of type "" +
                    ""ObjectId or an objectid representable integer"")
```

to:

```python   
                  
elif isinstance(arg, (Row, Reference)):
    return self.object_id(long(arg['id']))

elif not isinstance(arg, (int, long)):
    raise TypeError(""object_id argument must be of type "" +
                    ""ObjectId or an objectid representable integer"" +
                    "" (type %s)"" % type(arg) )

```

This may fix the problem as it better aligns this behavior with base.represent(), or the exception will give type information for the failed conversion.                      ",{},,User,False
