7060,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-24 16:41:08+00:00,33884891,apache/incubator-airflow,6065051,milton0825,47359,apache,325878196,391781581,"@Fokko we have a use case for backfill such that we want to use the values passed through CLI in the SQL instead of the values defined in params.

Let's look at the following example
```
templated_command = """"""
    echo ""text = {{ dag_run.conf.text if dag_run.conf.text else params.text }}""
""""""

bash_operator = BashOperator(
    task_id='bash_task',
    bash_command=templated_command,
    dag=dag,
    params={""text"": ""normal processing""}
    )
```

In the daily processing we will have the following output:
```
test = normal processing
```

In the backfill if we pass {""text"": ""backfill processing""}, we will have the output:
```
test = backfill processing
```

I hope this answers your question!",{},NONE,User,False
