7261,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-02 00:44:24+00:00,23458977,facebook/facebook-python-ads-sdk,21694597,daphyFB,69631,facebook,198244228,269927020,"Hi, 

Thanks for reporting SDK issues!

Yes, we return a Cursor object (which is like an iterator) because those querying APIs could have a large number of objects returned, which might hit the API limits.

You can use the ""build_objects_from_response"" method, or ""get_one"" method of the Cursor object to get some returned objects, which type should be ""AdsInsights"".

The Cursor class definition is here:
https://github.com/facebook/facebook-python-ads-sdk/blob/master/facebookads/api.py#L683

Please let me know if this doesn't solve your question, and/or if you have further questions or requests.

Thanks!
