7380,IssueCommentEvent,2015-05-26 19:42:16+00:00,788264,zeromq/pyzmq,151929,minrk,109777,zeromq,41664498,105644602,"The System Python on OS X is used for system functionality, and it can be problematic to install things with it. There are a variety of issues, including security problems. System Python is not kept up to date, and is frequently broken for one reason or another.

[virtualenv](https://virtualenv.pypa.io/en/latest/) is a tool for isolating installation of Python packages so they don't interfere with each other. Using these avoids some (not all) of the problems with OS X System Python. If you don't know what it is, I probably wouldn't recommend using it, because it can complicate managing installation.

I typically recommend [conda](http://docs.continuum.io/anaconda/install.html) to novice Python users on OS X and Windows, especially those who want to use scientific packages. Or you can get Python.org binaries from [the website](https://www.python.org/downloads/) or [brew cask](http://caskroom.io/). Or you can install Python with [Homebrew](http://brew.sh/).",{},,User,False
7382,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-27 09:42:39+00:00,788264,zeromq/pyzmq,151929,minrk,109777,zeromq,260842040,332467943,"You can't run poll in a subprocess. `socket` only exists in the parent process. When you fork the subprocess to call poll, the subprocess doesn't have a socket to poll on anymore.

What is your ultimate goal?",{},OWNER,User,False
