7401,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-11 13:05:08+00:00,30642061,sanger-pathogens/ariba,27732,satta,130803,sanger-pathogens,248460419,321806950,"I see. Well, as I said with most packaged versions of ariba that use dependencies to other packaged versions of bowtie2 the user would need to manually download the required version and set `ARIBA_BOWTIE2`. It might be useful to probably state this in the README because I figure that most users would intuitively want to go with the latest version even if not using the packaged ariba.

Regarding the current issue, for me the most important part here is that the tests fail, and that is currently breaking our builds, threatening ariba's existence in Debian altogether. What would you think about the following approach:
 - During the tests, check whether the version of Bowtie2 present matches the one you expect to behave like you want it to (mapping all the reads it should map).
 - If this is the case, fail the test with an error if unmapped reads occur in the test output.
 - If this is not the case, do not fail the test, but prominently display a notice message that the version of Bowtie2 present on the system is not the supported version and that you can only guarantee best results with the version you recommend (I remember that's how it was done in circlator(?) as well).
",{},,User,False
