7609,IssueCommentEvent,2015-07-24 21:21:59+00:00,3877327,guardian/alerta,615057,satterly,164318,guardian,96939701,124728745,"The [`reject`](https://github.com/guardian/alerta/blob/master/alerta/plugins/reject.py) plugin that enforces certain alert policies is just an example of what is possible and should be configured for different install environments, customised to enforce different alert policies (eg. only allow a subset of severity levels) or disabled if not required.

Configurable settings...
```
ORIGIN_BLACKLIST = [
    re.compile('foo/bar'),
    re.compile('qux/.*')
]

ALLOWED_ENVIRONMENTS = [
    'Production',
    'Development'
]
```

To disable, just override the `PLUGINS` setting in your environment-specific `alertad.conf` file to replace this:
```
PLUGINS = ['reject']
```
with this:
```
PLUGINS = []
```
