7655,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-02 23:29:19+00:00,35100117,neo4j/neo4j-python-driver,10504993,mikayla-grace,201120,neo4j,145273831,230127054,"We're now having some success with the py2neo 3.1 HTTP protocol ingesting large amounts of data into Neo4J 3.0.3.  Graph() does not accept a timeout parameter, it probably should.  Instead we set http.socket_timeout to a large value and our ingestion scripts have not thrown any exceptions.  If they do, we'll let you know.  Some of our scripts run for several days and it seems likely a socket timeout may throw spurious exceptions making it difficult to track.  Perhaps the Bolt transport is timing out as well on long runs.  However, we cannot find a way to set a timeout for Bolt.  Bolt works for us for any script that runs for less than 20 hours or so.  It hangs when a script runs for several days.",{},,User,False
7656,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-18 16:16:35+00:00,35100117,neo4j/neo4j-python-driver,224130,EmilStenstrom,201120,neo4j,162682839,233378307,"This problem is likely just an extra comma after `friend`: 

```python
for friend, in session.run(...)
