7657,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-07 09:00:49+00:00,35100117,neo4j/neo4j-python-driver,275311,nigelsmall,201120,neo4j,161511691,231022465,"This behaviour occurs because `session.run` is lazy. That is, no network activity occurs until you begin to consume the result. This allows for more efficient network usage by bundling multiple requests into fewer network packets whenever possible.

You therefore do not need to close the session, merely consume the result by iterating through the records or using `result.consume()`.",{},,User,False
7660,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-29 09:24:42+00:00,35100117,neo4j/neo4j-python-driver,1638145,lutovich,201120,neo4j,285044623,354420987,"Hi @manojgudi,

Driver does not expose such functionality in the interface. You could use `UNWIND` Cypher clause to provide query once with all needed params. See [this developer manual section](https://neo4j.com/docs/developer-manual/current/cypher/syntax/parameters/#cypher-parameters-create-multiple-nodes-with-properties).

Example might look like:

```python
query = ""UNWIND $names AS n CREATE (p:Person {name: n})""
names = [""abc"", ""pqr""]
with driver.session() as session:
    with session.begin_transaction() as tx:
        tx.run(query, names=names)
```

Hope this helps.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
