7827,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-07 14:03:54+00:00,648332,assimp/assimp,8821452,Breush,265533,assimp,320571873,387075002,"We might want to have an application-wide data fetcher, that can be used by the different importers.

```c++
// Default behavior: try to load a file from the filesystem.
// If the filename is relative, it should be to the root directory.
// Root directory might be empty when functions like ReadFileFromMemory are used.
std::vector<uint8_t> FetchFile(std::string filename, std::string rootDirectory);
```

And, we can add a hook:
```c++
void SetFileFetcher(std::function<std::vector<uint8_t>(std::string, std::string)> fileFetcher);
```

If this function is defined when `FetchFile` is called, we call it if we cannot resolve the file.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
