8338,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-30 15:25:25+00:00,38108816,biolab/orange3-text,713026,nikicc,555189,biolab,157325591,222514574,"Hi Alexey. This are my recommendations about the functionality of this widget (since I haven't gone through the code yet). To ease the further discussion they are enumerated:

1. We should add a progress bar if possible. This tells the user that something is happening. 

1. Currently, tweets are appended to previous corpus on output. I.e. if I search for `sad` and get 100 tweets and then search for `happy` and get an other 100 tweets, I get a corpus of 200 tweets. Is there a way to disable this appending functionality? I agree that it can come in handy sometimes but it can be misleading on other occasions. I suggest this is an optional parameter/checkbox, which is turned off by default, somewhere in the widget (probably in controlArea).

1. Language=English does not seem to work. Nothing happens if I add language and click search again. It only works with `en`. It should also work with `English` etc. But before you try to fix this, check the next point.

1. I recommend using dropdown menu (with country flags) for languages, like we have it in Orange2 (Figure below). Also supporting country codes (en) and names (English) seem redundant. For my tastes country codes should be removed, since they are too technical and we should only keep the names.
![screen shot 2016-05-30 at 15 50 23](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/713026/15651771/d3ca29ee-2681-11e6-93b8-e587c69ce2d9.png)

1. `X tweets have been downloaded` this should maybe be in `controlArea` in `Info` bow. For example look at `Corpus Viewer` in text or many other widgets in core Orange. Check if this looks better than current version, which is kind of strangely positioned IMHO.

1. `Max tweets` should be moved below language so that query is higher. Query should be on top, while `max tweets` is less important so it should be lower down the list.

1. What if user wants to get all the tweets? Should the user guess what is the maximum number of tweets and set `max tweets` accordingly. Could we somehow allow downloading all tweets?

1. API credentials dialog box could probably have just one button (OK). Cancel seem redundant, since you can just close this window. Also, having both check & OK seem redundant. If you click and everything is OK than this credential dialog should close. If you click OK and the key is invalid, then this windows should remain open and the user should be notified that the key is invalid. Also, instead of message`API key is/ is not validated!` could we use standard Orange warning/error? If all is OK the dialog will close anyway. If the key is invalid we should just add a warning at the top of dialog and keep it open.

1. Multiple search queries should be separated by newline rather than by space. Separating by space prevents searching for bigrams (e.g. Barack Obama). 

1. `created_at` field should be a TimeVariable, not a StringVariable.

1. Raising of errors/warnings is missing. In the previous case (Language=English) nothing happened and there was no warning/error raised. If user type in language that is not supported, a warning should be raised. I know we will replace languages with dropdown but keep this in mind as a general guideline.

1. Could you also add a Report button? 

1. Please, add some tests. Currently codecov checks fail due to this.",{},,User,False
