8570,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-22 13:00:25+00:00,79510167,pypa/pipenv,954310,techalchemy,647025,pypa,307537602,375296140,"Yes I understand that the test passes running python3 pipenv into a 2.7 environment. The test case was my idea. 

The goal of pipenv is to have a resolver that when you run it on python 3, resolving a python 3 environment, it also includes optional packages that would only be installed on python 2. The goal of pipenv is not to arbitrarily force tests to pass

This is why I said before that these tests should always pass as-is. Not because I forgot that apscheduler resolves funcsigs for python 2, but because we rewrote the resolver specifically around this test case. 

I am going to close this because this test exists for a reason
",{},MEMBER,User,False
