8685,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-12 14:57:40+00:00,27086567,scrapinghub/dateparser,1377457,pganssle,699596,scrapinghub,159093474,225439407,"@waqasshabbir FYI, some of this stuff may be appreciated upstream in dateutil. I'm currently focused on getting timezone-related improvements out for the 2.6.0 release, but the next thing on my list is an overhaul of how dateutil's parser works to make it much more modular and allow better specifications. I took a cursory look at what you've done and it looks like you're taking a similar approach to what I was thinking. Relevant issues where I talk about this are dateutil/dateutil#125, dateutil/dateutil#123, dateutil/dateutil#214 and dateutil/dateutil#268.

Not sure how reusable any of this stuff would be, but if you were interested in making a PR to help out, it would be much appreciated. Feel free to shoot me an e-mail (my e-mail is on the [dateutil github](https://github.com/dateutil/dateutil)) if you want to talk about details.",{},,User,False
