8703,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-15 06:15:42+00:00,3409513,twisted/klein,716529,glyph,716546,twisted,195954145,315513207,"> I have a bunch of URLs for my application somewhere; I need to use them in places other than the route decorators because elsewhere I want to have links to them, and I always use these constants.

One potential issue / antipattern with this idiom is that the parametric portions of the URL which cause Klein to pass you extra arguments are now hidden behind an extra layer of indirection.  Maybe this is just fine, but it feels like a slightly odd departure from the way klein apps usually co-locate their parameter descriptions and their function declarations.

On the other hand this is consistent with the ongoing work on #126 , which does move the form parameters to be somewhat more distant from the method definition.  So I'm kinda just thinking out loud here.",{},,User,False
