8792,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-04 17:43:48+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,723615,emmett9001,779641,Parsely,104920330,137802801,"@zsimpson Here's the [messy script](https://gist.github.com/emmett9001/ad8c8a1ab66325887f5b) I used to test this, and here's a [possible solution](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/pull/256). It would be great if you could try the patch against your use case and see how it works. Note that it's normal for the thread count to increase by exactly one after starting and stopping N consumers on the same client - when one consumer opens the offsets channel connection on the broker, it stays open for the lifetime of that `Broker` (keeping the thread alive). The script running against the patched version demonstrates that even if you start twenty consumers concurrently and then stop them all, the total thread count has only increased by one (the expected behavior).",{},,User,False
