8875,IssueCommentEvent,2015-01-23 19:55:04+00:00,14448779,astropy/astropy-helpers,676149,embray,847984,astropy,52297487,71254836,"As to my second issue, the `Model.name` property, it seems that autodoc does not propertly handle (the admitted rare, but not unheard of) case where a class attribute is also a property on the class's metaclass.  In the case of `Model` there *is* a a `name` property defined in the `Model` class, but there is also a `name` property defiend in the `_ModelMeta` metaclass.  `getattr(Model, 'name')` ends up evaluating the `name` property on the metaclass and returning a string, instead of just returning the `property` *object* for name.  Going to have to give that one a bit more thought, since this might affect a few other things in the modeling package.  But it's probably mostly only limited to that package....",{},,User,False
8880,IssueCommentEvent,2015-02-25 16:54:22+00:00,14448779,astropy/astropy-helpers,676149,embray,847984,astropy,58504630,76000146,"On a broader note, there's been an effort (currently on hold) to develop an improved interface for managing build-time dependencies that doesn't rely on easy-install, so in the meantime I don't want to encourage widespread use of this sort of hack.",{},,User,False
