9063,IssueCommentEvent,2015-03-27 03:06:25+00:00,9252533,numenta/nupic,4612954,macrintr,1039191,numenta,63969614,86799658,"@RDaneelOlivav & @rhyolight: I'm not active on this project anymore, but happy to offer my web searching expertise. 

Seems like the top of those error messages is an issue between PyAudio and Ubuntu that can be fixed per [StackOverflow](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/15182336/pyaudio-does-not-work-and-bricks-sound-on-ubuntu). 

And the bottom of those errors seem to indicate that the 'ufs' variable on line 252 needs to be cast as an int type (i.e. `ufs = numpy.unique(rfs).astype(numpy.int32)`). Play around with that. I'm guessing that the encoder input requirements changed when @scottpurdy updated the BitMapArrayEncoder to SparsePassThroughEncoder ([b418e7cae18af32b135915117414327020cbbe1c](https://github.com/numenta/nupic/commit/b418e7cae18af32b135915117414327020cbbe1c)).",{},,User,False
