9072,IssueCommentEvent,2015-04-03 20:30:34+00:00,9252533,numenta/nupic,239726,scottpurdy,1039191,numenta,58682741,89411476,"When we create algorithm implementations we start out with the concepts (cells, columns, layers) and figure out how to implement them in an efficient and modular way. So if some specific algorithm implementation is inefficient or unnecessarily confusing (like if it could be implemented with an array of Column classes without losing memory/speed efficiency) then we can discuss it. But this issue as written is way too general to be actionable.

Feel free to open an issue with a proposal for a specific algorithm but you will need to include a compelling rationale.",{},,User,False
