9105,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-10 02:20:13+00:00,16366081,numenta/nupic.core,364113,mrcslws,1039191,numenta,196246956,271468010,"@scottpurdy 

1. There are two pieces here that keep repeating: Reading inputs and allocating outputs. I tested both of these pieces in the other PR earlier today: https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/pull/1196#discussion_r95275635
2. Good point. I just added a `NumpyVectorWeakRefT` to handle the C boilerplate. I still like having the explicit Python methods which choose whether to coerce inputs into a numpy array, into a certain dtype, into a sorted array, etc.
3. This experience is managed in the python methods in the .i file. In most cases it will quietly convert it to the proper dtype via numpy.asarray. It won't log a comment when it copies the array. In a couple cases it's important to provide the right dtype, and the Python code handles this explicitly, e.g. here: https://github.com/mrcslws/nupic.core/blob/6cf9983bbdf5aab608b5df05dd0911269471962c/src/nupic/bindings/sparse_matrix.i#L1555",{},,User,False
