9509,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-06 01:19:53+00:00,4973632,pydata/patsy,609896,njsmith,1284191,pydata,226312672,299606638,"There's nothing built-in, but you can [use an arbitrary contrast matrix or define your own coding scheme](https://patsy.readthedocs.io/en/latest/categorical-coding.html). The former just involves passing a matrix with your desired coding to `C(...)` (there are examples in that link); the latter would look something like (untested but hopefully gives the idea):
```python
class Quadratic(object):
    def code_with_intercept(self, levels):
        cm = patsy.Poly().code_with_intercept(levels)
        # with_intercept coding has 0th, 1st, 2nd order terms = 3 terms total
        return patsy.ContrastMatrix(cm.matrix[:, :3], cm.column_suffixes[:3])

    def code_without_intercept(self, levels):
        cm = patsy.Poly().code_without_intercept(levels)
        # without_intercept coding has 1st & 2nd order terms = 2 terms total
        return patsy.ContrastMatrix(cm.matrix[:, :2], cm.column_suffixes[:2])

dmatrix(""y ~ C(a, Quadratic)"")
```
",{},,User,False
