9655,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-09 18:56:50+00:00,82729529,google/python-fire,1598379,jtratner,1342004,google,263578281,335255014,"Perhaps you could specify a prefix for environment variables (similar to
how npm and pip have env vars like npm_config_foo to set the foo value)?
The prefix could even be customizable.

I'd be hesitant to accidentally leak, say, my AWS access key to a function
just because it happened to have a matching keyword arg.

So, say prefix was FIRE_

Then FIRE_HOST=myhost FIRE_NPROCS=3 FIRE_GENOME=hg19 python something.py

Would translate to --host=myhost --nprocs=3 --genome=hg19

What happens with '-' by the way? Would that be transparently handled?
