9940,IssueCommentEvent,2015-02-17 06:27:13+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,11033304,YovavGad,1505683,FortAwesome,56211063,74622760,"Had the same issue. this is how I solved it:
Make sure the woff2 MIME type is being recognized by the web server... dahhh...
In my case - updating Web.config

  <system.webServer>
    <staticContent>
      <remove fileExtension="".woff"" />
      <remove fileExtension="".woff2"" />
      <mimeMap fileExtension="".woff"" mimeType=""application/font-woff"" />
      <mimeMap fileExtension="".woff2"" mimeType=""application/font-woff2"" />
    </staticContent>
</system.webServer>",{},,User,False
