10350,IssueCommentEvent,2016-08-17 18:35:22+00:00,35882519,zalando/connexion,1304950,sdementen,1564818,zalando,171594018,240505487,"Sorry for the terse description. Here some more info.

If you run the app.py in the zip file and head to http://127.0.0.1:5009/api/dogs you will see the stacktrace.
The controller called for this endpoint is the following
```
def get_dogs():
    return connexion.problem(status=403,
                             type=""ItemNotFound"",
                             title=""Dogs not found !"",
                             detail=""No dogs at all !"")

```
and the relevant swagger description is
```
paths:
  /dogs:
    get:
      operationId: ""app.get_dogs""
      summary: ""Get dogs""
      responses:
        200:
          description: ""Dogs found""
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/Dog'
        403:
          description: ""Item not found""
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/Error'

```
with the model being
```
definitions:
  Dog:
    type: ""object""
    properties:
      name:
        type: string
  Error:
    type: ""object""
    properties:
      status:
        type: integer
        description: HTTP status code
        example: 404
      type:
        type: string
        description: Type of error
        example: ItemNotFound
      title:
        type: string
        description: Humand friendly title of the error
        example: Item not found
      detail:
        type: string
        description: Detailed description of the error with contextual information
        example: The project with id '45fa5946-83e2-4531-90c8-926e15d6e748' was not found.

```
