10542,IssueCommentEvent,2015-10-19 19:01:28+00:00,39371927,glue-viz/glue-3d-viewer,13411839,PennyQ,1926209,glue-viz,106283227,149313721,"Just put the code and instructions from Vispy group here when the version of Vispy in Conda is updated to 0.5 https://github.com/PennyQ/Test/blob/master/volume_test_axis.py
* 1. Make your axis like `XYZAxis(parent=viewbox)` rather than `XYZAxis(parent=viewbox.scene)`. This allows you to define the position of the axis relative to the viewbox's coordinates in the GUI (so it stays fixed to the window instead of the internal scene).
2. Connect to the `viewbox.scene.transforms.changed` event and update the orientation of your axes to match. How you do this will depend on the type of camera you are using.
3. Make this into a visual of its own and submit a PR  :) 
",{},,User,False
