10552,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-06 14:52:41+00:00,37136408,algolia/algoliasearch-django,1821404,PLNech,2034458,algolia,288143613,363445909,"Hi @abakar, it seems your follow-up email slipped through last week. Sincere apologies for that.

I spent the day investigating further, see the open PR #241 which adds two tests that seem to confirm expected behavior:
- If you define settings in your [registered `AlgoliaIndex`](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-django#quick-start), those are applied when you reindex
- If you don't set specific settings when registering your Model, your current settings are kept over reindex.

Can you check if your app defines settings by registering a custom `AlgoliaIndex` subclass? 
- If it does, this explains the settings being reset: defining `settings` in your `AlgoliaIndex` subclass is a way to get these settings applied when reindexing (which indeed means you would lose any other setting in that index)
- If it doesn't, could you share here the code where you call `algoliasearch.register` and the definition of any mentioned Model / AlgoliaIndex? This would help pinpoint the difference between our succeeding tests and your failing use-case. 
",{},MEMBER,User,False
