10607,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-29 07:54:40+00:00,46388888,genialis/resolwe-bio,1026716,mstajdohar,2120224,genialis,258475514,347780370,Please rebase,{},OWNER,User,False
10608,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-25 12:10:33+00:00,46388888,genialis/resolwe-bio,26635159,mzganec,2120224,genialis,291141100,360448870,"The changes proposed in this PR seem to be headed in the wrong direction. Originally, `Trimmomatic` failed with no parameters specified. In my opinion this is one of the correct outcomes. Alternatively, if we want a sure-fire process even with no parameters specified by the user, we can directly copy the reads and the `FastQC` analysis from the input to the output and issue a warning that nothing has been done.

Note how the process changes with this PR. If the user left an input unspecified before, this option was not used by the `Trimmomatic` tool. Now, this option is going to be used even if the user leaves the input unspecified because it's going to get set to the default value making [this check](https://github.com/genialis/resolwe-bio/pull/464/files#diff-bc4de4d8bd68ecb646d585f4cd130c29R364) redundant. Additionally, if the default values are specified for the inputs, setting `required: false` is not needed anymore.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
10609,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-23 19:33:26+00:00,46388888,genialis/resolwe-bio,1026716,mstajdohar,2120224,genialis,279363709,359904023,"@matyasfodor Please point out this is only relevant for Mac and Windows. For instance, start the note with: ""On Mac or Windows, Docker might complain about non-mounted volumes..."" There is no such Docker preferences in Linux.",{},OWNER,User,False
10629,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-25 22:34:12+00:00,59868262,aws/chalice,17886885,pyvotal-cguers,2232217,aws,258173160,332033236,"No. It is exactly the same payload. I copy/paste the same json data in `testData.txt` into the API Console test, so the tests are really comparable... unless I need to do something else in the console. For example I notice there is no ""Body Mapping"" section in the ""Integration Request"", so the body is passed through as is or I am missing something.

