10698,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-09 18:33:29+00:00,30509483,clab/dynet,398875,neubig,2374376,clab,277341042,350496505,"OK, I understand the problem at least. Basically before, there was a bug that caused us not to autobatch together the sum operation, which I fixed resulting in most of the other models to get faster. However, in the particular case of the RNNLM code that you posted, this interacts with our prioritization heuristic, and causes the final matrix multiply + softmax to not be batched across time steps. This is annoying, but not a bug, and the correct way to fix it will be by coming up with a better prioritization method.

And yes, I think having a better suite of tests is a good idea. The DyNet benchmark repository now is automatically testing the speed periodically, so we can probably start by working with that.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
