11034,IssueCommentEvent,2015-02-18 16:07:06+00:00,11031844,uqfoundation/dill,321534,mmckerns,2855931,uqfoundation,50248618,74890827,"@takluyver: I am very much all for `x` being treated like an `x`.  I accepted a pull request that did not account for `mode=""x""`, and this was the ""compromise"" as there was a lot of good work done to implement it as is.   I'm of the mindset that pickling should never do anything ""smart""… basically, you should `dump` and `load` to yield the same object… and not tweak the object to be more ""useful"", as that usually means you are introducing fragility, confusion, and/or bugs of some sort.

I regard this ticket as a reminder that file `mode=""x""` needs attention.

