11168,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-25 02:56:56+00:00,4086616,shadowsocks/shadowsocks,18373361,hudson6666,3006190,shadowsocks,267049423,339198769,"@Mr-indescribable I have carried out an experiment these days. Since last time my vps where blocked, I changed its ip and created an iptables rule that drops all traffic to China.
```
ipset -N china hash:net
wget http://www.ipdeny.com/ipblocks/data/countries/cn.zone
for i in $(cat cn.zone ); do ipset -A china $i; done
iptables -A OUTPUT -p tcp -m set --match-set china dst -m state --state NEW -j DROP
iptables -A OUTPUT -p udp -m set --match-set china dst -m state --state NEW -j DROP
