11654,IssueCommentEvent,2015-07-29 20:04:52+00:00,8763405,SoCo/SoCo,1611076,KennethNielsen,3826649,SoCo,93124523,126081029,"Actually, having looked at it a little more I think the -e trick is really neat and the version that we should include in the doce. I guess people that want to modify the path of their virtual environment knows how. I will have a look at the docs and propose a change for you to review.

Just for the record. The way to modify the path in a virtual environment (at least on Linux and I guess Mac) is to edit the bin/activate script (which is a bash script) and add a line at the end along the lines of:

