11810,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-08 14:57:35+00:00,14991049,nccgroup/Scout2,17128601,saryx123,4067082,nccgroup,285676361,355988786,"@l01cd3v my take on this is that it is rather clear, scout2 is designed to help identify security faults with aws enviornments. To do that, a scout2 should provide (along the comprehensive platform) a report that is 
- clear(simple, informatively and instinctively titled & structured), 
- human readable (English, simple csv or paragraph format)
- concise (provide only the must-have info to begin remediation)
- actionable (simple users must be able to read it, forward it via email, etc) - .csv or .pdf format

As for the output format, rows and cells, **attached is a draft format for your convenience**. MetaSploit, AWS Trusted advisor and others provide similar exports. But they're all lacking in other/similar areas, thats why i'm here. 
[Cloud Audit Desired Format.zip](https://github.com/nccgroup/Scout2/files/1611907/Cloud.Audit.Desired.Format.zip)

If I had a scout2 export in such a format a few months ago when I was working for a bank, I wouldnt have sent it over to ops for remediation and my CISO(informative cc) that very moment;
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17128601/34676210-c5ac433c-f494-11e7-9dd6-db2984eeed78.png)

Tell me how I can help, if you believe that this aligns with Scout2 purpose and vision.

-Alex G.",{},NONE,User,False
