11882,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-06 15:25:25+00:00,53143022,oduwsdl/ipwb,2514780,machawk1,4416806,oduwsdl,269991200,342182214,"`firstRun()` in `util.py` is the source of the initial part of this error report, as it intentionally does not contain a CRLF combo so the line can be ""rewritten"" using just a CR from 0/4->1/4 as the retries are attempted. An error in this retry process highlights an issue with this assumption in that an error is reported between a retry iteration, stdout is soiled, and the retry and main processes halt.

`ome.warc` is a clipped version of the `SAMPLE_WARC` variable with a default value of `'samples/warcs/salam-home.warc', which is oddly clipped due to the CR/CRLF manipulation for line rewriting per above.

The part of the retry attempt string is from `indexer.py` from the string builder `attemptCount` within the fall-through exception handler. It would normally state, ""IPFS failed to add, (URI). retrying attempt (X/4)"". The final part of this error is displayed only in part because of the (again) CR-based line rewriting.

Part of this ticket may be moot, as (per ticket #??), the replay system ought to work regardless of the IPFS daemon's running state. Regardless, the console reporting described here ought to be fixed.",{},OWNER,User,False
