12553,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-14 16:31:15+00:00,53438969,globus/globus-cli,6373786,aaschaer,6120321,globus,206364301,294186020,"After some investigation while working on `globus rm`, it seems that the filter parameter for ls supports using `*` and `?` globbing, but not `[ ]`, whereas delete task globbing supports all three. 

It seems very confusing to users if
`globus rm` (and `globus delete` if we want?) accepts `*` `?` and `[ ]`
`globus ls` accepts `*` and `?` but *not* `[ ]`
and `globus transfer` can't use globbing at all.

Are good docs enough for this, or should we wait for the API to make it possible to be consistent with our globs accross the board?",{},,User,False
