12660,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-17 20:28:25+00:00,77478378,ethereum/py-evm,9263930,hwwhww,6250754,ethereum,288491872,358434352,"#### Changelogs
Refactored `VM` and `VMState` for avoiding to update `state_db` in `VM` level.
1. Moved the reward methods from `VM` to `VMState`.
2. Pick partial logic from `VM.mine_block()` to `VMState.finalize_block(block)` method.

* Now the only one special case of ""updating `state_root` manually in VM level” under `evm` is [the DAO fork header initialization](https://github.com/hwwhww/py-evm/blob/18578f1ca25e0a2dc45f003eac9e8f4579be8dc5/evm/vm/forks/homestead/headers.py#L89-L90).
* Under `tests`, I also added 3 lines to update `state_root` manually in VM level for setup the JSON fixtures test cases, but I think it's fine if only for the testing setup.
* With these changes, we also got clear `VM.create_block(block)`.
",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
