12740,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-26 01:13:12+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1418419,kalefranz,6392739,conda,203012534,275282955,"I'm not sure if #4433 fixes this, but we're sure going to try it.  This error is really weird, and google isn't helping me...

The line throwing the error is

    with open(conda_meta_full_path, 'w') as fo:

The `open` function we're using is actually `io.open`, and you're experiencing this with python 2.7.  The exception message is

    LookupError: unknown encoding:

`io.open` optionally takes an encoding argument.  So it's sort of an ""empty string"" unknown encoding.  

Given all of this, I'm hopeful that #4433 fixes the issue, but I can't myself reproduce it so I can't be sure.",{},,User,False
