12745,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-16 13:51:38+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,2797735,mcg1969,6392739,conda,154942333,219429810,"I think you'll find [this section of the documentation](http://conda.pydata.org/docs/using/envs.html) useful. If you're determined to use Aaron's conda package you'll need an environment with Python 2.7 and NumPy 1.7. The easiest way to get it is with this command:
```
conda create -n scitools_env -c asmeurer scitools python=2.7
```
`conda` will automatically select the version of NumPy needed. Then you can do
```
source activate scitools_env
```
to switch over to that environment and use it.

Finding a more recent version of scitools, or one that is compiled against a newer version of NumPy, is beyond our scope here. You'll need to build it yourself or find someone else who can.",{},,User,False
