12755,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-17 15:13:46+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1418419,kalefranz,6392739,conda,201276966,273196465,"@Korijn Each feature release series spends several weeks in canary.  It's the `conda-canary` channel on anaconda.org.  4.3.0, 4.3.1, 4.3.2, and 4.3.3 were never released to defaults.

Even for patch versions, releases are always uploaded to the canary channel first so that various stakeholders have an opportunity to test them.  It'd be awesome if you participated! :)

I think I've fixed ""Uncaught backoff with errno 41"" recently with https://github.com/conda/conda/pull/4277/commits/fb2a783d9b9371559b5ea82aaf8ae631c2ce0450.  I guess there could be further places to ignore it.

> Package cache is broken

#4297 might fix this for you as well.  If not, please help with more details and I'll get whatever is broken fixed asap.

> Dependency resolution has changed

This should absolutely not be happening.  Are you seeing this when using conda alone, or only in conjunction with conda-build?

",{},,User,False
