12787,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-23 01:49:14+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,334496,ilanschnell,6392739,conda,184617932,255564691,"When environment variables are required, I think it is important the set these environment variables explicitly, and not let `source activate` set then for you.  There have been suggestions to add setting other environment variables, such as `LD_LIBRARY_PATH`, which I am even more strongly opposed of.  Personally, I think that `source activate` should only set (or better modify) `PATH`, and things internal to conda (such as `CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV`).",{},,User,False
