13243,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-01 23:48:03+00:00,4127088,Azure/azure-sdk-for-python,1050156,lmazuel,6844498,Azure,137645044,190971345,"Hi,

Unfortunately, the `VirtualMachine` REST API which we use only gives the reference:
https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/azure/mt163682.aspx

Moreover, `Network` is not the same client of `Compute` and they are two separate packages with no inter-dependencies.

So, you have to do something like this:
```python
vm = compute_client.virtual_machines.get('vm1', 'vm1')
network_interface_full_id = vm.network_profile.network_interfaces[0].id
network_interface_short_id = network_interface_full_id.split('/')[-1]
network_interface_details = network_client.network_interfaces.get('vm1',network_interface_short_id)
print(network_interface_details.location)
```",{},,User,False
