13556,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-05 19:16:15+00:00,3060959,certifi/python-certifi,1382556,Lukasa,7292629,certifi,219685404,291966836,"Thanks for the suggestion!

That is not how certifi works. Certifi is just directly the contents of Mozilla's cert database. Until and unless it is added there, it will not be added here. As it happens it's not enormously important, because LE's root cert is cross-signed by a root that *is* in our trust bundle, so LE certs validate just fine.",{},,User,False
13559,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-19 13:50:46+00:00,3060959,certifi/python-certifi,1382556,Lukasa,7292629,certifi,229617563,302708130,"@jayfk Well, I should note that we still trust WoSign and will still trust Symantec. In these instances Mozilla is using ""graduated"" trust; that is, those CAs are partially trusted. We cannot express that in certifi. 

For that reason, all the changelog would contain is which CAs are added and removed. We could do that, but I'm not sure how valuable that would be. ",{},,User,False
