13566,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-22 02:02:12+00:00,23984796,jupyter/nbgrader,83444,jhamrick,7388996,jupyter,163692446,274302145,"It's really nice that you've structured it already to have the two steps of extract and collect, because I do think that separation is perfect. However, I think some of the logic that is in the collect step is perhaps more appropriate for the extract step. Here's my suggestion:

1. The extract step comes with a plugin that will examine the full path (before extraction) and determine the student id from that. By default maybe we can make it just like you have it---i.e. based on the filename or the name of the archive.
2. The extract step will then extract files (or copy them, if they are not an archive) to a path that includes the student id, such as `{downloaded}/{assignment_id}/{extracted_directory}/{student_id}`.
3. The collect step will now be able to determine the student id from the path. By default again it can just assume the files are flat in the extracted directory, but you can write a plugin to change this.",{},,User,False
