13579,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-29 03:24:16+00:00,23984796,jupyter/nbgrader,83444,jhamrick,7388996,jupyter,176408188,311852151,"Demo of the current interface that I have:

![](http://i.imgur.com/4VvZNsp.gif)

Not all the functionality works yet, but the browsing mostly does.

I'm not totally in love with the navigation on the left-hand-side, because I think it's not very clear what the difference between ""manage submissions"" versus ""gradebook"" is. The main difference is that under ""manage submissions"", the view is assignments-->students-->notebooks, whereas under ""gradebook"" the view is assignments-->notebooks-->students. The reason to have two different views like this is because nbgrader is structured to collect and autograde on a per-student basis, but then do manual grading on a per-notebook basis. I'm not sure what language I could use that would make this distinction clearer.",{},,User,False
