13836,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-17 17:35:19+00:00,1199632,schematics/schematics,52256,lkraider,7866441,schematics,274759241,345311026,"Hi, schematics has this feature, for example, to select only filled fields on serialization:

```python
from schematics.models import Model
from schematics.types import StringType
from schematics.common import NONEMPTY

class User(Model):

    name = StringType()
    password = StringType()
    email = StringType()
    phone_number = StringType()
    avatar = StringType()


user = User({""password"": ""123""})
print(user.serialize(export_level=NONEMPTY))
{'password': '123'}
```

You can also set the option only on the fields you want:
```python
class User(Model):

    name = StringType(export_level=NONEMPTY)
    password = StringType()
    email = StringType()
    phone_number = StringType()
    avatar = StringType()
(...)
print(user.serialize())
{'password': '123', 'email': None, 'phone_number': None, 'avatar': None}
```

More info here:
https://github.com/schematics/schematics/pull/372",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
