13935,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-13 21:15:03+00:00,24375248,blockstack/blockstack-core,7452680,jackzampolin,8165984,blockstack,304920027,372820878,"One way to do this would be to fold the `blockstack api start` into the `blockstack-core start` command and then driving which interfaces are available through options in the configuration file. We would need to need to change the `Dockerfile` and the shape of our deployments if we do this, but it might be worth it for the simplicity gain. We could eliminate an entire component from most deployments allowing users to run them together, or split them apart when needed to handle scaling or network concerns.

If we maintain a `v0.19` branch and make the `Dockerfile` changes there we will have auto builds of the new image and I will be able to build and test the new architectures quickly. We are also moving deployments to `gcloud` so this would be a good time for a change like this.

Documentation and the integration test environment would need to be changed anyway so the additional time there would not be too large. I'm interested to hear what you think about that idea.

Alternately either of the above options work for me. I would prefer to pass the `https://url.to.the.indexer.core.node` param as a config option rather than as an arg however. 
