13958,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-13 05:42:47+00:00,7803088,pylast/pylast,1324225,hugovk,8259519,pylast,182653724,253419535,"Thanks for the report. Unfortunately Last.fm redesigned (""reimagined"") their website in August 2015 and also broke their API. They've been slowly adding things back, but there still remains lots of broken stuff. They've also removed a lot from their API docs page, and we don't know if they're coming back. 

pylast's `User.get_neighbours ` calls Last.fm's `user.getNeighbours`:

https://github.com/pylast/pylast/blob/develop/pylast/__init__.py#L3334-L3350

They removed it from their docs at http://www.last.fm/api sometime after January 2016:

https://web.archive.org/web/20160113041418/http://www.last.fm/api
https://web.archive.org/web/20151023082634/http://www.last.fm/api/show/user.getNeighbours

I've reported this to Last.fm:
https://getsatisfaction.com/lastfm/topics/user-getneighbours-invalid-method-no-method-with-that-name-in-this-package
",{},,User,False
