14076,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-03 18:46:03+00:00,39858489,juju-solutions/charms.reactive,6385185,mbruzek,8684561,juju-solutions,120237415,161744011,"```bash
root@ip-172-31-22-252:~# which charms.reactive.sh
/usr/local/bin/charms.reactive.sh
root@ip-172-31-22-252:~# which -a charms.reactive.sh
/usr/local/bin/charms.reactive.sh
root@ip-172-31-22-252:~# charms.reactive.sh
This file contains helpers for developing reactive charms in Bash.

Usage:

    source `which reactive.sh`

    @when db.ready cache.ready
    function write_configuration() {
        db_dsn=$(state_relation_call db.ready uri)
        cache_uri=$(state_relation_call cache.ready uri)
        chlp render_template db_dsn=$db_dsn cache_uri=$cache_uri
    }

    @when_not db.ready cache.ready
    function report_blocked() {
        status-set blocked ""Waiting for db and/or cache""
    }

    reactive_handler_main

Helpers available:

  @hook PATTERN                Run decorated function if hook matches
  @when STATES                 Run decorated function if states are active
  @when_not STATES             Run decorated function if states not active
  @when_file_changed FILENAME  Run decorated function if file(s) changed
  @only_once                   Run decorated function only once
  set_state                    Set / activate a state
  remove_state                 Remove a state
  relation_call                Call a method on a relation by relation name
  state_relation_call          Call a method on a relation by active state
  all_states                   Check all states are active
  any_states                   Check any states are active
  name_relation_get            Get a relation value by relation name (vs ID)
```",{},,User,False
14077,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-16 14:18:41+00:00,39858489,juju-solutions/charms.reactive,119220,tasdomas,8684561,juju-solutions,234826223,309038165,@johnsca - restricted context hooks and charms.reactive don't mix. There's a lot of layers that depend on things like hookenv.config being available in any hook context. The solution to this will most likely be unrestricting restricted hook contexts. Until then it's best not to use charms.reactive for restricted context hooks.,{},,User,False
