14139,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-09 19:55:05+00:00,53977862,PyCQA/flake8-bugbear,55281,ambv,8749848,PyCQA,321701228,387856212,"Thanks for your report!

Flake8 is a primitive linter which doesn't understand which type does your name hold. Most of `iteritems()` is in fact invalid. In fact, even in Pandas, `iteritems()` is just an alias over the `items()` method.

What I'm suggesting is either:
* listen to the linter and rename `iteritems()` to `items()` for Pandas usage as well; or
* disable B301 in your .flake8 config.

As much as I would like the warning to be smarter, this is impossible with the view of the world that Flake8 provides.",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
