14176,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-13 07:26:43+00:00,24245737,projectmesa/mesa,395821,rht,8754505,projectmesa,255916417,343835033,"The reason why it is 40 for https://github.com/projectmesa/mesa/issues/410#issuecomment-343377912 test case, given the params x_max = 70, y_max = 20, x_min = -30, y_min = -30, x_center = 20, y_center = -5, width = 100, height = 50: for the y coordinate, y = -15 - (-5) = -10 and -10 modulo 50 is 40 instead of -10.

I think the less opaque solution is to multiply the size with a sign of the x and y coordinate.
```
if self.torus:
    pos_1 -= self.center
    pos_1 = pos_1 % np.sign(pos_1) * self.size
    pos_2 -= self.center
    pos_2 = pos_2 % np.sign(pos_2) * self.size
```",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
