You are closing the connection. Don't close it.

Why don't you take a look at the JS example https://github.com/tinode/example-react-js and just do it the same way?",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
14557,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-25 04:05:45+00:00,26661222,tinode/chat,5938143,or-else,9325720,tinode,268258340,339208107,"Hi Riandy,
 
* `{del what=topic}` will actually delete the topic for everybody if it's issued by the topic owner. Only the owner can delete the topic. 
* If `{del what=topic}` issued by a non-owner, it's equivalent to `{leave unsub=true}`
* And yes, `{del what=topic}` can be issued without subscribing first while `{leave unsub=true}` requires subscribing.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
