14661,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-03 14:33:03+00:00,66641037,LonamiWebs/Telethon,6297805,Lonami,9887454,LonamiWebs,239383187,326808600,"> Is it true?

It used to be true. Scheme changes. You can see all the versions [here](https://github.com/stek29/tl-schema).

> Why the implementation of core.telegram.org differs from the scheme.tl file?

Because they're outdated as heck. Do not rely on [core.telegram.org](https://core.telegram.org) documentation, unless you use Telethon with a layer as outdated as [23](https://core.telegram.org/schema). Things may not work, and you'd have to generate the code on your own. Not hard, just replace the `scheme.tl`, run the generator, and do some adjustments

The scheme [Telethon uses](https://lonamiwebs.github.io/Telethon/methods/auth/send_code.html) doesn't have the `sms_type` parameter, probably removed some time ago now. So, the process described here is the only way to request a SMS now it seems.",{},OWNER,User,False
