14866,IssueCommentEvent,2015-02-12 19:56:54+00:00,533328,pyelasticsearch/pyelasticsearch,295816,erikrose,10234413,pyelasticsearch,20042302,74140889,"The context manager turned out to be a bad idea, because sending would be triggered on an arbitrary enqueuing operation, so you'd have to wrap each in a try/except if you wanted to handle (or even ignore) any errors. Also, there was no good way to get at the response from the request sent as the context manager exited. So the solution is bulk_chunks(): http://pyelasticsearch.readthedocs.org/en/latest/api/#pyelasticsearch.bulk_chunks.",{},,User,False
