14901,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-06 11:28:08+00:00,14284859,marshmallow-code/marshmallow,304265,frol,10334301,marshmallow-code,211954927,284371441,"I am talking about these lines: https://github.com/marshmallow-code/marshmallow/blob/596015ad86676c74a11879c88a2aa69e91b0d40c/marshmallow/schema.py#L84-L97. You infer the `ordered` option there and since you already treat the schema as ordered, it is absolutely fine to help the SchemaOpts to set the `ordered` value correctly.

This behavior was introduced 2 years ago in https://github.com/marshmallow-code/marshmallow/commit/927704be32a999b5c65edaa8ee6f76e58fe6890a to close #162.",{},,User,False
