15043,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-23 10:43:53+00:00,103890505,ConsenSys/mythril,7359555,FFengIll,10818037,ConsenSys,328171277,407015935,"Some extra suggestion: (for I am doing some work like it)
Makes stack element as a individual class like Slot/Element or something.
The possible benefits are:
* python `magic` to override some operators, e.g. __add__, __lt___ and so on
```python
class Slot:
    def __iadd__(self,other):
       #inplace add
       self.value = self.value + other.value
       return self.
```
* python `property` to insulate solver and some others, e.g. (main)
```python
if type(condi) == BoolRef
# can be changed to
if condi.is_bool_ref()
```
* make it possible to use mythril but work for another vm / bytecode (minor)
* may more

I am not sure which one is the better, but wish to have a quick discuss.",{},NONE,User,False
