15184,IssueCommentEvent,2016-08-26 04:40:33+00:00,51452284,globality-corp/microcosm,477722,jessemyers,11172782,globality-corp,173311607,242628755,"What about something like:

```
class Opaque(object):
    ...
    @contextmanager
    def bind(self, key, value):
        if key in self._store:
            present, old = True, self._store[key]
        else:
            present, old = False, None
        try:
            self._store[key] = value
            yield self
        finally:
            if present:
                self._store[key] = old
            else:
                del self._store[key]
```

This gives you the composable syntax:

```
with opaque.bind(""bar"", ""baz""):
     with opaque.bind(""this"", ""that""):
          ...
```

Even more useful as a decorator (different impl required):

```
@route(""/foo/<bar>"")
# decorator would extra the ""bar"" argument from kwargs
@opaque.bind(""bar"")
def some_route(bar):
    pass
```",{},,User,False
