15235,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-01 18:07:32+00:00,18302786,IDSIA/sacred,1160920,Qwlouse,11296960,IDSIA,211158621,283420485,"That's a good question. Not sure. I'll have to think about this one.
One thing that sacred already provides is the possibility of overwriting a run from the database. 
This is meant to support later usage of MongoDB as a scheduling mechanism. 
ATM this can only be done by adding a MongoObserver from python code and setting its `overwrite` field to the database entry that should be overwritten. It will check for source-code consistency and then update that entry instead of making a new one. 
