15361,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-19 10:51:31+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,3085284,NikolajBjorner,11668813,Z3Prover,303014316,406236226,"I have been looking at it since yesterday and wasn't able to reproduce it on the master branch either, and the other examples time out too.
The 4.6.0 bits also seem to not be able to reproduce it (trying just a few random seeds).
The more systematic test is to try several variants of smt.random_seed=<NN> to take into account differences in pre-processing orders. The even more systematic approach is to perform a wider bisection search for where the changed behavior differs. I don't have a proper setup or cycles for this today/this week and there is a good chance that the findings will be that indeed some bug that got fixed between the version from March and now took care of it. It is still rather useful to know the root cause given that the latest example seems pretty straight-forward and satisfiable. 
Note that Z3 had very major churn during May - early July. 
This should now be going back for some time to the more mundane update cycles for general stability.

",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
