15756,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-02 14:19:33+00:00,51397392,pytroll/satpy,2157033,RutgerK,13004956,pytroll,342658379,409943029,"Good point, and you're right. The test fail because of the same issue. 

Both tests use a hard-coded separator, similar as it is in the yaml config files. I think that's fine, since it is the starting point. But the yaml reader class parses these patterns before calling the functions that now fail. They fail because the tests don't perform this parsing step. 

Parsing the pattern happens at:
https://github.com/pytroll/satpy/blob/master/satpy/readers/yaml_reader.py#L99

Unfortunately the parsing is not a separate function, so tests can't use the same code without having a instantiation of the yaml reader class. 

I've added the parsing step to the tests just to see what AppVeyor makes of it. But it's of course bad practice to put the logic in the test itself. But what would be the best way to resolve that?  I can move that line to a separate function which both the tests and the yaml reader can use.",{},NONE,User,False
