16154,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-25 10:39:02+00:00,46374199,IntelRealSense/librealsense,22448952,aangerma,14095512,IntelRealSense,317266408,384242852,"Hi @zuru 
I investigated the issue and it can occur whenever the `stream_profile` object passed to `open` was created from a different instance of the same device. 

To illustrate, the following snippet will reproduce the same problem:
```cpp
rs2::context ctx;
rs2::syncer s;
rs2::device d1 = ctx.query_devices()[0];
rs2::device d2 = ctx.query_devices()[0];

d2.first<rs2::depth_sensor>().open(d1.first<rs2::depth_sensor>().get_stream_profiles().front());
d2.first<rs2::depth_sensor>().start(s);
s.wait_for_frames();
```
Despite `d1` and `d2` both being created from same physical device, they are treated by the `syncer` as distinct entities. As a result the `syncer` fails to handle frames with stream profile from a ""different"" device.

We should certainly resolve the crash, but as a work-around you should avoid referencing the same sensor from multiple API objects. ",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
