Not sure if it's the cause of the `No device detected` issue -- I encountered an error when running `./scripts/patch-uvcvideo-ubuntu-mainline.sh`
```
Reading package lists... Done
Building dependency tree       
Reading state information... Done
Picking 'linux-lts-wily' as source package instead of 'linux-image-4.2.0-27-generic'
The following packages have unmet dependencies:
 libudev-dev : Depends: libudev1 (= 204-5ubuntu20.18) but 204-5ubuntu20.19 is to be installed
```

This unmet dependency issue is solved by:
1. Adding these two lines in `/etc/apt/sources.list`
```
deb http://us.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ trusty-updates main    
deb-src http://us.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ trusty-updates main
```
2. Run `sudo apt-get update` and then `sudo apt-get install libudev-dev`. Rerun `./scripts/patch-uvcvideo-ubuntu-mainline.sh`

But the F200 is still not detected when running the example in `/bin/`. Tested with two F200 and the problem is the same. Both F200s' F/W are [confirmed](https://software.intel.com/en-us/forums/realsense/topic/562071) to have F/W 2.60.0.0 by running Intel's DCM (`intel_rs_dcm_f200_1.4.27.41944.exe`) on Win10.


