17001,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-23 22:47:54+00:00,53549881,anymail/django-anymail,639984,medmunds,17517617,anymail,290968629,359958010,"It would certainly make sense for the test EmailBackend to generate a unique message_id for each recipient. PR welcome.

I'm also open to the idea of a separate console backend. (If you find this is replicating a lot of code from the existing test backend, feel free to refactor to share code if that seems cleaner.) 

BTW, there's an undocumented test EmailBackend feature where you can [set `anymail_test_response`](https://github.com/anymail/django-anymail/blob/v1.2/anymail/backends/test.py#L37-L47) on a message, either to a dict with a `""recipient_status""` key mapping recipient email to `AnymailStatus` ([example](https://github.com/anymail/django-anymail/blob/v1.2/tests/test_send_signals.py#L103-L107)), or to an `AnymailAPIError` instance to simulate a failure. This probably isn't all that useful for your integration tests, but can be helpful for email unit tests.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
17004,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-20 18:51:11+00:00,53549881,anymail/django-anymail,639984,medmunds,17517617,anymail,275171054,345791261,"That's the right idea. Your CustomEmailBackend should just subclass Django's BaseEmailBackend directly, and it needs to return the number of messages ""delivered"" (queued). Something like:

```python
from django.core.mail.backends.base import BaseEmailBackend
from .tasks import async_send_messages

class CustomEmailBackend(BaseEmailBackend):
    def send_messages(self, email_messages):
        async_send_messages.delay(email_messages)
        return len(email_messages)
```

See Django's (brief) docs on [defining custom email backends](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/stable/topics/email/#defining-a-custom-email-backend).

Also, you should plan for your `async_send_messages` task to occasionally fail -- ESPs have API downtime, network routes develop temporary glitches, etc. You can probably use something like Celery's [`Task.retry`](http://docs.celeryproject.org/en/latest/reference/celery.app.task.html#celery.app.task.Task.retry) to gracefully handle [`AnymailAPIError`](https://anymail.readthedocs.io/en/stable/sending/exceptions/#anymail.exceptions.AnymailAPIError) exceptions.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
