17100,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-07 11:30:40+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,6504915,bmw,17889013,certbot,239436017,313657232,"When `--preferred-challenges` was added in Certbot 0.9.0, there was a bug where the value was not saved for renewal. This was [fixed in Certbot 0.10.2](https://github.com/certbot/certbot/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#0102---2017-01-25). If you last issued the certificate with one of the older versions of the client, this could happen.

If you run the same `certbot certonly ...` command you provided above with Certbot 0.10.2+ to obtain a certificate, the `--preferred-challenges` value should be saved. Keep in mind the renewal configuration file is only updated if you actually obtain a certificate. If you select option 1 at the prompt below, the file will not be modified:
```
You have an existing certificate that has exactly the same domains or certificate name you requested and isn't close to expiry.
(ref: /etc/letsencrypt/renewal/mycert.conf)

What would you like to do?
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1: Keep the existing certificate for now
2: Renew & replace the cert (limit ~5 per 7 days)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Select the appropriate number [1-2] then [enter] (press 'c' to cancel):
```
Sorry for the trouble!",{},,User,False
