17107,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-07 07:02:24+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,482089,domcleal,17889013,certbot,160782725,230999220,"Interesting question! I don't think there's going to be any real difference, I can't think of an example right now that would be a problem, but I would tend towards using aug.get to retrieve that /path node.  The only disadvantage is that it only works with a file path (`/files/etc/foo.conf`), and not say, a VirtualHost node beneath the path (`/files/etc/foo.conf/VirtualHost/bar`), where that suffix has to be stripped first.",{},,User,False
