17159,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-31 16:27:57+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,220205,jsha,17889013,certbot,157047764,222743369,"One or the other is better, not both. I've gone back and forth about which approach I prefer, and I'm definitely interested in your thoughts. I think `--prefix` is a flag that describes what it *does*, which is appealing to us as developers. I think `--user` (or `--nosudo`) is a flag that describe what the user wants to accomplish, which probably makes easier to understand and more appealing for end-users. So right now I'm leaning towards that.",{},,User,False
