17173,IssueCommentEvent,2016-09-06 19:22:52+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,1174866,jaywink,17889013,certbot,171552532,245060768,"Is there a reason why a [proper changelog](http://keepachangelog.com) isn't maintained? It doesn't have to cover the time before the changelog, and if enforced in the PR level, it will maintain itself and be ready to publish at release time.

Certbot is used by millions. Making users browse commit logs to find out when some new cli flag was added so they know if they can support it in their automation thingy (for example, might have just spent 30 minutes looking for something like that ;)) is just not very user friendly.

I realize the promise is to fix this in 1.0, but is there a reason that cannot start now?",{},,User,False
