17331,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-04 23:05:28+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,310139,hackaugusto,19666847,raiden-network,219311483,291666505,"The same transfer going through the same node is not necessarily a loop. Consider the corner case represented by the following subgraph (arrows represent direction of the messages):

![raiden](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/310139/24682414/1bac4d46-1989-11e7-8ee9-568c4f6fa05c.jpg)

- A transfer from A to G must be mediated through B.
- B has 3 routes available with an equal number of hops
  - Suppose that B's choice is `B-C-T-G`
- If T does not have enough capacity in the `TG` channel then it must try a different route
- T uses the path `T-D-B-E-F-G`, making use of the node B again",{},,User,False
