17585,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-02 08:38:17+00:00,76210069,pytorch/text,3007947,mttk,21003710,pytorch,318744686,385905136,"From what I can see, the issue is probably due to the [pool method](https://github.com/pytorch/text/blob/master/torchtext/data/iterator.py#L271) which uses a fixed size length lookahead to sort the bathces. 

Essentially, moving `lookahead * batch_size` examples from (train/test/val) set, sorts them and generates batches of approximately same length. So if you perhaps have a dataset of size (lookahead + 1), the last batch is going to be taken as-is (even if the examples are of length 5, 100 and 1000).

Apart from doing what you said (using packed sequences), you can probably set the `padding_idx` in the `nn.Embedding` to 1 (which is the torchtext default) and *you should* get similar results. 

Alternatively (and probably best), set batch_size to `1` in test / valid.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
