17784,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-30 20:46:04+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,13382316,RosadinTV,22243823,streamlink,277970138,348315673,"@fozzysec Yes, i like the idea of this addition.
Some ideas to implement it could be:
1) Your index file idea.
Pros: Get all plugins checksum at once without limit.
Cons: Updating the index file of plugins
2) Rely on Github API to index the files ([link](https://api.github.com/repos/streamlink/streamlink/contents/src/streamlink/plugins))
Pros: Get all plugins checksum at once without the need of updating an index file.
Cons: There is a rate limit of 60 request per hour for unauthenticated requests.
3) My idea of shrinking main repository.
Pros: Replace whole plugins folder to the latest one at once (avoiding the need to compare the checksum of each plugin and download them one by one) without limit.
Cons:  You couldn't known when plugin updates really exist, since only the ETag of the master.zip would be taken into account.
4) Use simple HTTP requests (without using the API) to get data (like we do with mostly all the Plugins).
Pros: No limits and can be combined with other methods/ideas.
Cons: It may stop working if Github changes the website design.

Sure there are many other ideas, but this is what I can think of at the moment 😆 ",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
