18050,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-21 07:32:38+00:00,79083614,python-trio/trio,440661,lilydjwg,26335827,python-trio,283777031,353279003,"I use `list.remove` in my version, which will be slow when there are a lot of deadlines. Tornado and pyftpdlib clean up the heap like you said. That needs some bookkeeping.

SortedDict has a dict and a list. It uses bisecting to find the value to remove and remove it from the list. This will take more memory than a heap, but there is no cleanup that comes up and take up a bit time.

curio has a good idea, but it still needs some kind of periodic work. It will be interesting to see which one is faster.

Thanks for the explanation 👍 

PS: you seems to have pasted a wrong link.",{},NONE,User,False
