18384,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-14 11:53:49+00:00,4334538,rq/django-rq,483024,johnhuffsmith,35203774,rq,317472463,397267896,"You're correct; in my experience it's an uphill battle getting EB to do anything outside it's design.  You will quickly need to fall down to EC2-like manual tweaking on the boxes (package installs, pre/post deploy tasks/apache configs).  You can script it all with .ebextensions, but it's fragile and you'll need to figure all of it out on your own.

If you want that level of deep integration, you'll need to let the infrastructure service you choose dictate the application design details. Either ditch RQ and use the native EB worker daemon via SQS, roll something custom, or explore other hosting options (Heroku, EKS, etc)",{},NONE,User,False
