18528,IssueCommentEvent,2011-12-02 23:33:00+00:00,527040,recurly/recurly-client-python,868721,perryism,144605,recurly,2260646,2997437,"I had to retrieve the plan_code like you didn.  Not sure if you figured that out yet.  If you just wanted to get the plan_code and don't care about hacking(cuz I am not sure if there is a right approach),  this is my solution.  I overwrote the __getattr__ method in Subscription

class Subscription(Resource):

    ...................................

   def __getattr__(self, name):
        if name == 'plan_code':
            name = 'plan/plan_code'

        return super(Subscription, self).__getattr__(name)",{},,,
